---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Ang Mingsong">
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="hero-eyebrow">4 years as an engineer <span class="accent-dot">·</span> 15 years telling the stories of engineering</p>
    <h1 class="hero-headline">I didn't come here with answers. I came with <em>stories.</em></h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">Somewhere in them, you might recognise a piece of your own. Where are you in yours?</p>
  </section>

  <section class="profiles-section">
    <p class="profiles-label">Where are you in yours?</p>
    <div class="profiles-grid">
      <a href="/stories/the-room-changed-when-i-did?profile=1" class="profile-card">
        <h2>I'm doing good work. Why do the opportunities keep passing me by?</h2>
        <p>The people who just know how to talk keep getting ahead. I don't want to play that game. What else am I supposed to do?</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/stories/i-didnt-choose-this-path-then-i-did?profile=2" class="profile-card">
        <h2>I'm considering a change.</h2>
        <p>Can I take on a role outside of what I was trained for? Can I succeed beyond engineering? What if I fail?</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/stories/the-room-changed-when-i-did?profile=3" class="profile-card">
        <h2>I started a business. Building it was supposed to be the hard part.</h2>
<p>The product works. The clients who've tried us come back. But growth? That part doesn't seem to follow the same logic. What am I getting wrong?</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="all-stories-link">
    <a href="/stories">Read all stories →</a>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
